						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup near the Mosque [front face].</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Nityavarsha [Indra III]. 10th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record in cursive characters refers to the rule of Nityavarsha <hi rend="italic">Śrī Prithvīvallabha</hi> [Probably Rāshṭrakūṭa Indra III]. It mentions a <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍaḷēśvara</hi> (name not clear) and the place Baḷḷaniṭṭage. The purport seems to record a grant but not clear. </p>						

						<p>It may be placed to early 10th century A.D. on the basis of a reference to Nityavarsha but not certain.</p>						

						</summary>
